snippet.textDisplay:
Ok so Mykie talking about the waste of PR boxes since she and other makeup-artists simply get too much. I had an idea, which isn't necessarily directed towards Mykie but any makeup-oriented channel that would be interested in trying this out.
What about a youtube series in which the youtuber sends out the PR they receive but can't use to followers or smaller youtubers who are just getting started, and these will do an unboxing and review on them. They would fill in a simple Google Form if they're interested, someone works these out and sends them and the receivers review it and send the info/video/writtenreview back. The shipping costs could be earned back easily if the series go well.
This way the products don't go to waste, the companies still get their views, it will be a more open and honest review and more people can enjoy it.
In theory it'd be a good solution right? I don't know how it would work out in practise though... I hope Mykie or any other bigger channel can see this comment to think about it.

snippet.textDisplay:
So... to be honest, my make-up collection was never as big, but still, it took me years to downsize. My main problem was that I did not wear Make-up on a daily basis, but I enjoyed it to do my Make-up just for me at home, or to special events, like birthdays and stuff.
I did not declutter by the Conmarymethod, because I did not know that system. However, I looked at my stuff with the knowledge, that I want to get rid of some of it. So whenever I felt overwhelmed by the amount of stuff, I threw out a bit. Also I wanted to use as much of my stuff as possible, hence that Make-up was really expensive for me at the time an should not go to wast. So using up those products and slowly deciding what I want to buy new took quiet some time.
Now I just own one red Lipstick and an Eyeshadowpallet I paint my eyebrows with. For special occasions I borrow mascara and stuff from a roommate.
